    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "The name Queens Village emerged in 1923 when the Long Island Railroad added “Village” to avoid confusion with the county.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        13
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://urbanareas.net/info/resources/neighborhoods-queens/queens-village-queens-history/"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The neighborhood was first settled around 1816 by English settlers and named for its midpoint between Williamsburg and Jamaica.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        4
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_Village%2C_Queens"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "A factory for French Company telephone booths once stood where Metro Mall now sits.",
